The fired employee took revenge, bought laptops for the company and sold them
A disgruntled employee bought computers for the company and then sold them.
He managed to spend the money before being arrested by the police.
In a short period of time, the man bought a total of sixteen computers in twelve cases for more than two hundred thousand crowns.
"After the takeover, he took the notebooks to Olomouc, where he sold them in bazaars," said Rostislav Br?ckner, the chief commissioner of the Šumperk police.
The motive of the fraud was revenge to the employer for the dismissal and also to make money.
"He told us during the interrogation that he had used the money to pay off the loans," said Brueckner.
Police also found that the impostor was a pathological gambler who had been repeatedly treated in a psychiatric ward.
The money could also end up in slot machines or in video lottery terminals.
"The fact is that we didn't find any money on him," the commissioner said.
The fraudster, who has already been convicted of theft, now faces between one and five years in prison.
Police have not yet said whether they are also threatening to punish the bazaars that bought the notebooks under price and continued to sell them.
